ce:section.ce:para:
It is necessary to check the haemolytic activity in the plants or plant extracts before being used as a medicine or drug. Haemolytic activity results in lysis of the red blood cells by breaking the cell membrane which will lead to adverse effects, and may cause haemolytic anemia [26]. The haemolytic activity of the seed extract and PdNPs samples was tested at different concentrations ranging from 250 to 1000μg/mL (Table 3
                        ). At the highest concentration (1000μg/mL), the haemolytic activity of seed extract and PdNPs was 8.55% and 9.69% respectively (Fig. 5
                        ). At highest concentration of the positive control, Triton X-100 (1000μg/mL), the haemolytic activity was observed to be 90.62%.

The cytotoxic effect of HeLa cell lines was studied against P. emblica seed extract and PdNPs by MTT assay. As the concentration increases for the seed extract and PdNPs, the cell death percentage gradually increases; at the maximum concentration of seed extract and PdNPs (150μg/mL), it is able to kill around 58.00% and 65% respectively (Table 4
                        ) (Fig. 7
                        ). The IC50 values calculated for seed extract, PdNPs and positive control (Cyclophosphamide) were found to be 50.12μg/mL, 30.45μg/mL and 15.15μg/mL respectively.
